Sensa Risk Intelligence AML GA Integration Test Plan

Author: Ciaran Finnegan | Date: February 12, 2026 | Confluence report

Objective: Provide a structured, repeatable integration test strategy and execution steps for SRI AML GA data flows.

Integrated Test Plan Strategy

This section documents the integrated test strategy for the SRI AML GA release, aligned to the approved architecture.

The focus is on batch-only processing, MinIO-based ingestion, and the core flows between Sensa Data, Detection, Investigation, and Agents.

Scope and Objectives

  • Validate end-to-end batch data ingestion, AML inference, and investigation workflows across Sensa Data, Sensa Detection, Sensa Investigation, and Sensa Agent.
  • Confirm integration points between MinIO feeds, OLAP/OLTP stores, Kafka events, and investigation search.
  • Demonstrate the AML GA release operates in batch mode only and uses MinIO as the sole source feed.

Architecture Summary

  • MinIO feeds are ingested by Sensa Data (Data Connectors) and validated by Data Quality before landing in OLAP (Iceberg) and OLTP (PostgreSQL).
  • Sensa Detection ingests transactions directly from MinIO for AML Inference (batch) and uses OLAP data for training.
  • Decisioning Service enriches detection events with OLTP data and publishes Detection Events to Kafka.
  • Sensa Investigation consumes Subject Updated and Detection Events from Kafka and queries OLTP for search.
  • Sensa Agent capabilities (Operational Assistants and Investigator Copilot) are accessed from Investigation.

Test Approach

  • Exercise each integration flow with batch payloads aligned to the SRI AML GA IFS schema.
  • Validate positive flows and error handling (data quality failures, missing references).
  • Capture evidence from logs, Kafka topics, and UI/API responses for traceability.

Environments and Test Data

  • Use non-production MinIO buckets with controlled batch payloads (transactions, subjects, accounts).
  • Seed OLTP reference data required for enrichment and investigation search.
  • Use Kafka topics dedicated to test execution to isolate events and ensure clean assertions.

Entry and Exit Criteria

  • Entry: Batch ingestion endpoints available, Kafka topics provisioned, and OLAP/OLTP accessible.
  • Exit: All integration test cases executed with expected results and defects triaged.

Integration Flows Under Test

  1. MinIO -> Sensa Data (Data Connectors) -> Data Quality -> OLAP/OLTP
  2. MinIO (direct) -> AML Inference (batch) in Sensa Detection
  3. Data Quality -> AML Inference trigger
  4. OLAP (historic data) -> Sensa Training
  5. AML Inference -> Decisioning Service -> Kafka Detection Events
  6. Sensa Data -> Kafka Subject Updated Events -> Sensa Investigation
  7. Sensa Investigation -> OLTP Transaction Search
  8. Sensa Investigation -> Sensa Agent (Operational Assistants, Investigator Copilot)

Out of Scope

  • Real-time ingestion or streaming processing.
  • Data ingestion from sources other than MinIO.
  • Ontology-driven access for AML inference or investigation search.
  • Entity Resolution, Watchlist Management, and Data Mapping Agent.

Assumptions

  • SRI AML GA IFS schema is the agreed format for test data.
  • Kafka topics and schemas are available for Subject Updated and Detection Events.
  • OLTP contains required reference data for Decisioning enrichment.

Day Zero: Sanity Integration Tests (I1)

Short sanity checks to confirm core batch ingestion and investigation readiness for I1.

These tests are designed to be fast and unblock Day 1 and Day 2 execution.

DZ-I1-01: Subject updates into Investigation - happy path

Purpose: Validate I1 flow: Subject Updated Events

Traceability: Sensa Data -> Kafka Subject Updated Events -> Sensa Investigation

Test data notes:

  • Phase reference: Subject Updated Events
  • Generate synthetic data aligned to the SRI AML GA IFS schema.
  • Embed correlation IDs and timestamps for traceability.
  • Use deterministic subject, account, and transaction IDs for reconciliation checks.
  1. Prepare a minimal subject update batch with a unique run ID and deterministic subject/account identifiers.
    Expected: Batch validates against the SRI AML GA IFS schema with all mandatory fields present.
    Suggested data format: CSV/Parquet subject update file; strategy: synthetic records with consistent IDs and timestamps.
  2. Ingest the batch through Sensa Data and confirm Data Quality completion.
    Expected: Ingestion completes with a Data Quality pass status.
    Suggested data format: MinIO batch file plus Data Quality report output.
  3. Verify Subject Updated Events are published to Kafka with the run ID.
    Expected: Events match the ingested subjects and include correlation identifiers.
    Suggested data format: Kafka JSON payloads with subject_id, run_id, timestamp.
  4. Confirm Sensa Investigation reflects the updated subject details.
    Expected: Investigation case context displays the new subject attributes.
    Suggested data format: Investigation UI/API snapshot with updated fields.
  5. Capture traceability evidence across systems.
    Expected: Logs and payloads show consistent run IDs from ingestion to investigation.
    Suggested data format: Log extracts from Sensa Data, Kafka, Investigation.

DZ-I1-02: Subject updates into Investigation - error handling

Purpose: Validate negative scenarios for I1 flow: Subject Updated Events

Traceability: Sensa Data -> Kafka Subject Updated Events -> Sensa Investigation

Test data notes:

  • Phase reference: Subject Updated Events
  • Generate synthetic data aligned to the SRI AML GA IFS schema.
  • Embed correlation IDs and timestamps for traceability.
  • Use deterministic subject, account, and transaction IDs for reconciliation checks.
  1. Create a subject update batch with missing mandatory fields.
    Expected: Data Quality flags the batch as failed.
    Suggested data format: CSV/Parquet with missing subject identifiers or mandatory attributes.
  2. Confirm no Subject Updated Events are published to Kafka.
    Expected: Kafka topics show no new events for the run.
    Suggested data format: Kafka consumer output filtered by run ID.
  3. Verify Investigation does not apply the invalid update.
    Expected: Subject context remains unchanged for the affected IDs.
    Suggested data format: Investigation UI/API snapshot.

Day 1: Integration Tests (I2-I4)

Integration testing focused on Sensa Detection, Sensa Investigation, and the key I2-I4 data flows.

Validates Kafka event consumption, inference triggers, and investigation workflows.

D1-I2-01: Batch ingestion triggers AML inference - happy path

Purpose: Validate I2 flow: AML Inference Trigger

Traceability: Sensa Data -> Data Quality -> AML Inference trigger

Test data notes:

  • Phase reference: AML Inference Trigger
  • Generate synthetic data aligned to the SRI AML GA IFS schema.
  • Embed correlation IDs and timestamps for traceability.
  • Use deterministic subject, account, and transaction IDs for reconciliation checks.
  1. Generate a compliant transaction batch with risk-relevant attributes and a unique run ID.
    Expected: Batch passes schema validation and is accepted for processing.
    Suggested data format: Transaction CSV/Parquet with amounts, timestamps, counterparty IDs.
  2. Ingest the batch via Sensa Data and confirm Data Quality completion.
    Expected: Data Quality reports a pass status.
    Suggested data format: Data Quality summary report output.
  3. Validate the AML Inference trigger fires for the batch.
    Expected: AML Inference job starts for the run ID.
    Suggested data format: Inference job metadata with run ID.
  4. Confirm inference output contains risk scores linked to the original transactions.
    Expected: Each transaction has a risk score and traceable ID.
    Suggested data format: Inference output records with transaction IDs.

D1-I2-02: Batch ingestion triggers AML inference - error handling

Purpose: Validate negative scenarios for I2 flow: AML Inference Trigger

Traceability: Sensa Data -> Data Quality -> AML Inference trigger

Test data notes:

  • Phase reference: AML Inference Trigger
  • Generate synthetic data aligned to the SRI AML GA IFS schema.
  • Embed correlation IDs and timestamps for traceability.
  • Use deterministic subject, account, and transaction IDs for reconciliation checks.
  1. Prepare a transaction batch that violates Data Quality rules.
    Expected: Data Quality marks the batch as failed.
    Suggested data format: Transactions missing mandatory fields or invalid types.
  2. Confirm AML Inference is not triggered.
    Expected: No inference job is created for the batch.
    Suggested data format: Inference scheduler logs.
  3. Validate error reporting and triage evidence.
    Expected: Error logs include rule violations and batch ID.
    Suggested data format: Data Quality failure report.

D1-I3-01: Detection events generate investigations - happy path

Purpose: Validate I3 flow: Detection Events

Traceability: Decisioning -> Kafka Detection Events -> Sensa Investigation

Test data notes:

  • Phase reference: Detection Events
  • Generate synthetic data aligned to the SRI AML GA IFS schema.
  • Embed correlation IDs and timestamps for traceability.
  • Capture evidence artifacts (event payloads, transcripts, UI snapshots) for audit trails.
  1. Run AML Inference to generate high-risk detection events.
    Expected: Decisioning produces Detection Events for high-risk transactions.
    Suggested data format: Inference output with risk thresholds exceeded.
  2. Consume Detection Events from Kafka.
    Expected: Events are published with valid schema.
    Suggested data format: Kafka JSON with event ID, subject ID, risk score.
  3. Verify Investigation creates cases per event.
    Expected: Investigation cases include event ID and risk data.
    Suggested data format: Investigation case export.
  4. Validate event-to-case traceability.
    Expected: Case fields match event payload values.
    Suggested data format: Case comparison checklist.

D1-I3-02: Detection events generate investigations - error handling

Purpose: Validate negative scenarios for I3 flow: Detection Events

Traceability: Decisioning -> Kafka Detection Events -> Sensa Investigation

Test data notes:

  • Phase reference: Detection Events
  • Generate synthetic data aligned to the SRI AML GA IFS schema.
  • Embed correlation IDs and timestamps for traceability.
  • Capture evidence artifacts (event payloads, transcripts, UI snapshots) for audit trails.
  1. Publish a malformed Detection Event to Kafka.
    Expected: Investigation rejects or flags the event.
    Suggested data format: Kafka payload missing required event fields.
  2. Confirm no invalid case is created.
    Expected: Investigation UI shows no new case for the event.
    Suggested data format: Investigation activity log.
  3. Review error handling and alerting.
    Expected: Validation errors are logged with event ID.
    Suggested data format: Investigation error logs.

D1-I4-01: Direct transaction feed to AML inference - happy path

Purpose: Validate I4 flow: OLAP Access

Traceability: MinIO (direct) -> AML Inference (batch)

Test data notes:

  • Phase reference: OLAP Access
  • Generate synthetic data aligned to the SRI AML GA IFS schema.
  • Embed correlation IDs and timestamps for traceability.
  • Use deterministic subject, account, and transaction IDs for reconciliation checks.
  1. Prepare a direct MinIO transaction batch for Sensa Detection with a run ID.
    Expected: Batch is recognized by the direct ingestion job.
    Suggested data format: Transactions file with timestamps and counterparties.
  2. Trigger AML Inference via the direct feed.
    Expected: Inference job starts for the direct batch.
    Suggested data format: Inference job metadata record.
  3. Validate inference outputs and enrichment.
    Expected: Detection outputs include scores and enrichment data.
    Suggested data format: Inference output with risk scores.

D1-I4-02: Direct transaction feed to AML inference - error handling

Purpose: Validate negative scenarios for I4 flow: OLAP Access

Traceability: MinIO (direct) -> AML Inference (batch)

Test data notes:

  • Phase reference: OLAP Access
  • Generate synthetic data aligned to the SRI AML GA IFS schema.
  • Embed correlation IDs and timestamps for traceability.
  • Use deterministic subject, account, and transaction IDs for reconciliation checks.
  1. Upload a direct transaction batch with schema errors.
    Expected: Direct ingestion rejects the batch and logs validation errors.
    Suggested data format: Malformed transaction CSV.
  2. Confirm no inference run is triggered.
    Expected: Inference scheduler shows no job for the batch.
    Suggested data format: Inference scheduler logs.
  3. Capture error evidence for triage.
    Expected: Logs capture batch ID and error summary.
    Suggested data format: Error log excerpt.

Day 2: End-to-End Integration Tests (I5-I7)

Comprehensive end-to-end integration coverage across all Sensa Risk Intelligence applications.

Includes training, investigation search, and agent-assisted workflows.

D2-I5-01: Historical data drives training and inference - happy path

Purpose: Validate I5 flow: OLTP Access

Traceability: OLAP (Iceberg) -> Sensa Training -> AML Inference

Test data notes:

  • Phase reference: OLTP Access
  • Generate synthetic data aligned to the SRI AML GA IFS schema.
  • Embed correlation IDs and timestamps for traceability.
  • Seed OLAP history with at least one training period for model version validation.
  1. Seed OLAP with historical transactions covering at least one training period.
    Expected: OLAP partitions are available for the target period.
    Suggested data format: Iceberg partitions by date range.
  2. Initiate a Sensa Training run.
    Expected: Training completes with a new model version.
    Suggested data format: Training job metadata and model ID.
  3. Run AML Inference using the updated model.
    Expected: Inference metadata references the new model version.
    Suggested data format: Inference output with model version.

D2-I5-02: Historical data drives training and inference - error handling

Purpose: Validate negative scenarios for I5 flow: OLTP Access

Traceability: OLAP (Iceberg) -> Sensa Training -> AML Inference

Test data notes:

  • Phase reference: OLTP Access
  • Generate synthetic data aligned to the SRI AML GA IFS schema.
  • Embed correlation IDs and timestamps for traceability.
  • Seed OLAP history with at least one training period for model version validation.
  1. Attempt a training run with insufficient OLAP history.
    Expected: Training fails with a data sufficiency error.
    Suggested data format: OLAP dataset missing required partitions.
  2. Confirm inference continues to use the last stable model.
    Expected: Inference metadata shows the prior model version.
    Suggested data format: Inference output model metadata.
  3. Capture training failure diagnostics.
    Expected: Logs include missing data details and run ID.
    Suggested data format: Training error logs.

D2-I6-01: Investigation search against OLTP data - happy path

Purpose: Validate I6 flow: OLTP Access

Traceability: Sensa Investigation -> OLTP (PostgreSQL) transaction search

Test data notes:

  • Phase reference: OLTP Access
  • Generate synthetic data aligned to the SRI AML GA IFS schema.
  • Embed correlation IDs and timestamps for traceability.
  • Use deterministic subject, account, and transaction IDs for reconciliation checks.
  1. Ensure OLTP contains transactions from the latest batch load.
    Expected: OLTP rows exist for target transaction IDs.
    Suggested data format: OLTP query output by transaction ID.
  2. Execute Investigation transaction search with the known IDs.
    Expected: Search results return matching transactions.
    Suggested data format: Investigation search criteria payload.
  3. Validate field-level accuracy.
    Expected: Search results match OLTP values.
    Suggested data format: Comparison checklist for key fields.

D2-I6-02: Investigation search against OLTP data - error handling

Purpose: Validate negative scenarios for I6 flow: OLTP Access

Traceability: Sensa Investigation -> OLTP (PostgreSQL) transaction search

Test data notes:

  • Phase reference: OLTP Access
  • Generate synthetic data aligned to the SRI AML GA IFS schema.
  • Embed correlation IDs and timestamps for traceability.
  • Use deterministic subject, account, and transaction IDs for reconciliation checks.
  1. Search for a transaction that is absent from OLTP.
    Expected: Investigation returns no results.
    Suggested data format: Search criteria with nonexistent ID.
  2. Confirm error handling for missing data.
    Expected: UI/API returns a clear no-results message.
    Suggested data format: Investigation response payload.

D2-I7-01: Investigation to Sensa Agent assistance - happy path

Purpose: Validate I7 flow: Investigation Agents & Copilot

Traceability: Sensa Investigation -> Sensa Agent (Operational Assistants / Investigator Copilot)

Test data notes:

  • Phase reference: Investigation Agents & Copilot
  • Generate synthetic data aligned to the SRI AML GA IFS schema.
  • Embed correlation IDs and timestamps for traceability.
  • Capture evidence artifacts (event payloads, transcripts, UI snapshots) for audit trails.
  1. Open a case with multiple alerts and request Operational Assistant guidance.
    Expected: Assistant response references the case context and suggested actions.
    Suggested data format: Case summary including alert IDs and subject details.
  2. Request Investigator Copilot analysis on the same case.
    Expected: Copilot summary aligns with evidence and risk indicators.
    Suggested data format: Case timeline and evidence bundle.
  3. Capture assistant outputs for audit.
    Expected: Transcripts stored with case reference ID.
    Suggested data format: Assistant transcript export.

D2-I7-02: Investigation to Sensa Agent assistance - error handling

Purpose: Validate negative scenarios for I7 flow: Investigation Agents & Copilot

Traceability: Sensa Investigation -> Sensa Agent (Operational Assistants / Investigator Copilot)

Test data notes:

  • Phase reference: Investigation Agents & Copilot
  • Generate synthetic data aligned to the SRI AML GA IFS schema.
  • Embed correlation IDs and timestamps for traceability.
  • Capture evidence artifacts (event payloads, transcripts, UI snapshots) for audit trails.
  1. Request assistant output with incomplete case context.
    Expected: Assistant responds with a request for more information or flags missing context.
    Suggested data format: Case payload missing key fields.
  2. Verify assistant guardrails and logging.
    Expected: Logs capture the missing context warning.
    Suggested data format: Assistant interaction logs.
